__ http://osnews.com

Software
--------

New 1.20 version of the famous Commodore 8-bit computers line emulator 
VICE is available for all Amiga platforms, AROS included. You may find it `here`__.
WinAros is a preinstalled AROS environment installed on a HD image, compatible 
with famous virtual machines QEMU and Microsoft VirtualPC, both freely available on 
the net. You may download `QEMU Winaros here`__ and `VirtualPC one here`__. Heinz-Raphael 
Reinke has also written a complete `AROS installation on hard disk`__ in PDF format. 
If you prefer, there is also a `german version`__. You need Adobe Acrobat Reader 
to read them. 

__ http://www.viceteam.org/amigaos.html
__ http://amidevcpp.amiga-world.de/WinAros/WinAros_Light_QEMU.zip
__ http://amidevcpp.amiga-world.de/WinAros/WinAros_Light_VPC.zip
__ http://amidevcpp.amiga-world.de/WinAros/Aros_HD_Install_English.pdf
__ http://amidevcpp.amiga-world.de/WinAros/Aros_HD_Installation.pdf
